"legal.effectiveDate" = "Effective Date: May 28, 2026";
"legal.privacy.title" = "Privacy Policy";
"legal.privacy.section.1.title" = "1. Overview";
"legal.privacy.section.1.body" = "Habitdot is a simple habit tracking app that helps you create habits, add an optional purpose, check your progress, view widgets, and receive short motivational feedback. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.";
"legal.privacy.section.2.title" = "2. Information You Provide";
"legal.privacy.section.2.body" = "You may enter habit names, optional habit purposes, colours, frequency settings, reminder preferences, completion records, language settings, and appearance settings. During onboarding or when you contact us, you may also provide survey answers, how you heard about Habitdot, and free-form feedback, contact messages, or bug reports. Habitdot does not require you to create an account and does not ask for your name, email address, phone number, or contacts to use the core app.";
"legal.privacy.section.3.title" = "3. Local Storage and Widgets";
"legal.privacy.section.3.body" = "Your habit data is primarily stored locally on your device and in the app group container used by Habitdot and its Home Screen widgets. Widgets read this local data so they can display your selected habits and progress on the Home Screen.";
"legal.privacy.section.4.title" = "4. AI Motivational Feedback";
"legal.privacy.section.4.body" = "If AI feedback is available or enabled, Habitdot may send limited habit data to our server to generate a short daily message. This may include your habit titles, optional purposes, recent 7-day completion data, yesterday's completion status, today's date, locale, color information, and an app install identifier. We use this data to generate the feedback message, operate the service, prevent abuse, and improve reliability.";
"legal.privacy.section.5.title" = "5. Device and Technical Data";
"legal.privacy.section.5.body" = "When Habitdot communicates with our server, standard technical information such as IP address, request time, endpoint, response status, and basic device/network information may be processed by our hosting infrastructure for security, debugging, analytics, and service operation.";
"legal.privacy.section.6.title" = "6. Purchases and Subscriptions";
"legal.privacy.section.6.body" = "If you purchase Habitdot Pro, purchases are processed by Apple through the App Store and may be managed with a third-party subscription service such as RevenueCat. We do not receive your full payment card details. We may receive subscription status, product identifiers, transaction identifiers, and related purchase metadata needed to unlock Pro features and restore purchases.";
"legal.privacy.section.7.title" = "7. Notifications";
"legal.privacy.section.7.body" = "If you enable habit reminders, Habitdot may schedule local notifications on your device. Notification preferences are used to remind you about your habits and can be changed in the app or in your device settings.";
"legal.privacy.section.8.title" = "8. How We Use Information";
"legal.privacy.section.8.body" = "We use information to provide habit tracking, display progress, power widgets, generate optional AI feedback, maintain and secure the app, process purchases, restore subscriptions, respond to support requests, and comply with legal obligations.";
"legal.privacy.section.9.title" = "9. Sharing of Information";
"legal.privacy.section.9.body" = "We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited information with service providers that help us operate Habitdot, such as hosting providers, AI service providers, Apple, and subscription management providers such as RevenueCat. These providers process information on our behalf or under their own terms.";
"legal.privacy.section.10.title" = "10. Data Retention and Deletion";
"legal.privacy.section.10.body" = "Local habit data remains on your device until you delete it, uninstall the app, or reset your data. Server logs and AI service records may be retained for a limited period as needed for security, debugging, and service operation. You can delete habits in the app and may contact us through the Contact Us option in Settings for privacy-related requests.";
"legal.privacy.section.11.title" = "11. Children";
"legal.privacy.section.11.body" = "Habitdot is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided personal information, contact us so we can take appropriate action.";
"legal.privacy.section.12.title" = "12. Changes to This Policy";
"legal.privacy.section.12.body" = "We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the effective date and may provide notice in the app or through another appropriate method.";
"legal.privacy.section.13.title" = "13. Contact";
"legal.privacy.section.13.body" = "For privacy questions or requests, contact us through the Contact Us option in Habitdot Settings.";
"legal.terms.title" = "Terms of Use";
"legal.terms.section.1.title" = "1. Agreement";
"legal.terms.section.1.body" = "These Terms of Use govern your access to and use of Habitdot. By using Habitdot, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the app.";
"legal.terms.section.2.title" = "2. The Service";
"legal.terms.section.2.body" = "Habitdot helps you create habits, add optional purposes, track completion, view progress, use Home Screen widgets, and receive short motivational feedback. Habitdot is a self-improvement tool and does not guarantee any specific outcome, streak, health result, productivity result, or personal result.";
"legal.terms.section.3.title" = "3. Your Responsibility";
"legal.terms.section.3.body" = "You are responsible for the habits, purposes, notes, and other information you enter into Habitdot. You agree not to use Habitdot in a way that violates laws, infringes rights, attempts to disrupt the service, or misuses AI or server features.";
"legal.terms.section.4.title" = "4. AI Feedback";
"legal.terms.section.4.body" = "Habitdot may provide AI-generated motivational feedback based on your habit data. AI feedback may be inaccurate, incomplete, or not suitable for your situation. It is provided for general motivation only and is not medical, mental health, legal, financial, or professional advice.";
"legal.terms.section.5.title" = "5. Health and Safety";
"legal.terms.section.5.body" = "Habitdot is not a medical device or healthcare service. Before starting or changing habits related to exercise, diet, sleep, medication, mental health, or other health matters, consult a qualified professional when appropriate.";
"legal.terms.section.6.title" = "6. Subscriptions and Purchases";
"legal.terms.section.6.body" = "Habitdot may offer paid features such as Habitdot Pro. Prices, plans, trials, and included features may change over time. Purchases are processed through Apple using your App Store account. Subscriptions renew automatically unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period, according to Apple's subscription rules.";
"legal.terms.section.7.title" = "7. Cancellation and Refunds";
"legal.terms.section.7.body" = "You can manage or cancel subscriptions in your App Store account settings. Refund requests are handled by Apple and are subject to Apple's policies. Habitdot cannot directly issue App Store refunds unless Apple provides a mechanism for doing so.";
"legal.terms.section.8.title" = "8. License";
"legal.terms.section.8.body" = "We grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use Habitdot for personal, non-commercial purposes in accordance with these Terms and Apple's App Store rules.";
"legal.terms.section.9.title" = "9. Intellectual Property";
"legal.terms.section.9.body" = "Habitdot, including its design, code, branding, graphics, and content, is owned by us or our licensors and is protected by intellectual property laws. You may not copy, modify, distribute, reverse engineer, or create derivative works from Habitdot except as permitted by law.";
"legal.terms.section.10.title" = "10. Availability and Changes";
"legal.terms.section.10.body" = "We may update, modify, suspend, or discontinue parts of Habitdot at any time. We may also add, remove, or change free or paid features. We are not responsible for interruptions, data loss, or service limitations caused by device issues, operating system changes, network problems, third-party services, or events outside our reasonable control.";
"legal.terms.section.11.title" = "11. Disclaimer";
"legal.terms.section.11.body" = "Habitdot is provided on an \"as is\" and \"as available\" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, non-infringement, availability, accuracy, and reliability.";
"legal.terms.section.12.title" = "12. Limitation of Liability";
"legal.terms.section.12.body" = "To the maximum extent permitted by law, we will not be liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for loss of data, profits, goodwill, or other intangible losses arising from your use of or inability to use Habitdot.";
"legal.terms.section.13.title" = "13. Termination";
"legal.terms.section.13.body" = "You may stop using Habitdot at any time. We may suspend or terminate access to server-based features if you violate these Terms, misuse the service, or create security, legal, or operational risk.";
"legal.terms.section.14.title" = "14. Changes to These Terms";
"legal.terms.section.14.body" = "We may update these Terms from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the effective date and may provide notice in the app or through another appropriate method. Continued use of Habitdot after changes means you accept the updated Terms.";
"legal.terms.section.15.title" = "15. Contact";
"legal.terms.section.15.body" = "For questions about these Terms, contact us through the Contact Us option in Habitdot Settings.";
